				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Second Great War at Sea: Tropical Storm" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Second Great War at Sea: Tropic of Capricorn told the story of a war that never happened: a naval conflict between Argentina, Chile and Brazil breaking out in 1940 as part of the world-wide Second Great War. Tropical Storm picks up the story, as a German squadron arrives to aid the Brazilians and the naval war continues.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Second Great War is our alternative-history setting, in which American President Woodrow Wilson&amp;rsquo;s attempt to mediate an end to the fighting succeeds, leaving the great empires intact to fight again a generation later. War spreads around the globe, eventually engulfing the empires&amp;rsquo; South American allies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like all the other Second Great War at Sea games and books, Tropical Storm uses the rules from Second World War at Sea and is fully compatible with that series&amp;rsquo; historical games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tropical Storm includes a map (covering Argentina&amp;rsquo;s central coast) and 80 new die-cut, silky smooth playing pieces (60 &amp;ldquo;long&amp;rdquo; ship pieces and 20 standard-sized square ones). Thirty new scenarios move the story along, and put even more hot battleship action on your gaming table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tropical Storm is not a complete game. You&amp;rsquo;ll need a copy of Tropic of Capricorn (and only Tropic of Capricorn) to play its scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
